@startuml
title EA View - Multi-Agent Stock Recommendation & Monitoring Platform (v7.0 - Weighted P/E Quant + JSON Monitoring)

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 12
skinparam dpi 150

skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor #1F4E79
    LifeLineBorderColor #1F4E79
    LifeLineBackgroundColor #F8FBFD
    ParticipantBorderColor #1F4E79
    ParticipantBackgroundColor #F8FBFD
    ParticipantFontColor #1F4E79
    ActorBorderColor #1F4E79
    ActorBackgroundColor #F8FBFD
    GroupBorderColor #7F8C8D
    GroupBackgroundColor #F7F9FA
    BoxBorderColor #1F4E79
    BoxBackgroundColor #FAFCFE
}

actor User
participant "Portal / Streamlit UI" as UI
participant "Multi-Agent Orchestrator\n(LangGraph)" as ORCH

box "LLM SERVICE LAYER"
participant "Fast Tier\n[Claude Haiku 4.5]\nBuy & Monitor Rationale\n(Prompt Cache Enabled)" as LLMFAST
participant "Reasoning Tier\n[Claude Sonnet 4.6]\nIndustry / Validation /\nThesis Review" as LLMSMART
end box

note over LLMFAST, LLMSMART
  LLM Routing Policy:
  ─────────────────────────────────────
  Haiku 4.5 (Fast Tier) — high-volume, short-output tasks
    • buy_rationale per recommendation (2-3 sentences, free text)
    • monitoring_rationale per action → strict JSON {action, severity, rationale}
    • System prompts are cached: ~90% input token savings on repeated calls
  Sonnet 4.6 (Reasoning Tier) — low-volume, complex reasoning
    • industry_reasoning — multi-factor sector prioritization
    • qualitative_analysis — JSON-structured stock validation
    • thesis_review — nuanced INTACT / WEAKENED / BREACHED assessment
  ─────────────────────────────────────
  All LLM calls have deterministic fallback.
  LLM usage is opt-in via ANTHROPIC_API_KEY.
end note

box "Platform Data Sources"
collections "Market / Index Data" as MKT
collections "Financial Data APIs\n(Screener.in / NSE / yfinance)" as FIN
collections "Internet / News /\nReal-Time Signals" as NET
collections "Fund Holdings Data Provider\n(AMFI / Morningstar)" as FUNDAPI
collections "CAMS PDF / Manual MF Input" as MFINPUT
collections "Manual ETF / Direct Input" as ETFINPUT
collections "Geopolitical Signal Sources\n(MEA / PIB / RBI / NSDL / RSS)" as GEOAPI
database "SQLite Portfolio DB" as DB
participant "Monthly Refresh Scheduler\n[Cron / Trigger]" as REFRESH
end box

box "SIGNAL INTELLIGENCE LAYER"
participant "Geopolitical & Macro\nSignal Agent\n[LLM:Sonnet + Structured Sources]" as GEO
participant "Policy & Regulatory\nSignal Agent\n[Deterministic + LLM:Sonnet]" as POL
participant "FII / DII Flow\nSentiment Agent\n[Deterministic]" as FLOW
participant "Contrarian Sentiment\nDetector Agent\n[LLM:Haiku + Rules]" as CONTRA
participant "Signal Aggregator Agent\n[Deterministic + Rules]" as SIGAGG
end box

box "PORTFOLIO INGESTION LAYER"
participant "MF Holdings Parser Agent\n[LLM + PDF Parser]" as MFP
participant "ETF Holdings Fetcher Agent\n[Deterministic]" as ETFA
participant "Portfolio Exposure\nNormalization Agent\n[Deterministic + Ticker Map]" as NORM
participant "Overlap Analysis Agent\n[Deterministic + Rules]" as OVL
participant "Gap Identification Agent\n[LLM + Rules]" as GAP
end box

box "NEW BUY FLOW - Agent Layer"
participant "Index Member Agent\n[Deterministic]" as IDX
participant "Industry Recommendation Agent\n[LLM:Sonnet + Signal Aware]" as IND
participant "Stock Candidate Agent\n[Deterministic]" as CAND
participant "Quant Model Agent\n[Quality Moat Scoring]" as QBUY
participant "Risk Filter Agent\n[Deterministic + Multi-Source]" as RFILT
participant "Top-N Selection Agent\n[Deterministic]" as TOPN
participant "Qualitative Validation Agent\n[LLM:Sonnet + JSON Output]" as VALID
participant "Portfolio Differentiation Agent\n[Deterministic Rules + LLM]" as DIFF
participant "Entry Timing & Execution\nReadiness Agent\n[LLM + Contrarian Check]" as TIMING
participant "Position Sizing Agent\n[Deterministic + Rules]" as SIZING
participant "Tax & Cost Impact Agent\n[Deterministic]" as TAX
participant "Data Freshness &\nConfidence Agent\n[Deterministic + Rules]" as CONF
participant "Final Buy Recommendation Agent\n[LLM:Haiku + Cached]" as BUY
end box

box "MONITORING FLOW - Agent Layer"
participant "Signal Refresh Agent\n[Deterministic]" as SIGREF
participant "Industry Monitoring Agent\n[LLM + Signal Aware]" as PIND
participant "Individual Stock Monitoring Agent\n[LLM + Tool Use]" as PSTK
participant "Portfolio Quant Model Agent\n[Quant / Deterministic]" as QMON
participant "Thesis Review Agent\n[LLM:Sonnet + Hard Rules]" as PREV
participant "Drawdown & Risk\nAlert Agent\n[Deterministic]" as DRAW
participant "Decision Agent\n[LLM:Sonnet + Policy Rules]" as DEC
participant "Behavioural Guard Agent\n[Deterministic Rules]" as BGUARD
end box

== FLOW 0 : SIGNAL INTELLIGENCE PIPELINE ==

group 1. Geopolitical & Macro Signal Collection
REFRESH -> ORCH : Weekly signal refresh trigger
ORCH -> GEO : Collect and score geopolitical signals
GEO -> GEOAPI : Fetch MEA press releases\n(India foreign policy developments)
GEOAPI --> GEO : Official India diplomatic signals
GEO -> NET : Fetch curated geopolitical news\n(India-Pakistan / US-China / Middle East /\nRussia-Ukraine / India-EU FTA)
NET --> GEO : Geopolitical developments
GEO -> DB : Read user_macro_thesis override
DB --> GEO : User thesis (highest priority)
note right of GEO
  Geopolitical Signal Taxonomy:
  STRONGLY_POSITIVE / POSITIVE /
  NEUTRAL / NEGATIVE / STRONGLY_NEGATIVE

  Sectors mapped per signal:
  India-Pak tension escalation:
    Defence PSU     → STRONGLY_POSITIVE
    Aviation        → NEGATIVE
    Tourism         → NEGATIVE
  US-China decoupling:
    Electronics Mfg → POSITIVE
    IT Services     → NEUTRAL
  Oil price spike (Middle East):
    Macro India     → NEGATIVE
    OMCs            → NEGATIVE
    Renewables      → POSITIVE
  China slowdown:
    FII India inflow→ POSITIVE
    Commodity inputs→ POSITIVE
  India-EU FTA progress:
    Pharma exports  → POSITIVE
    Textiles        → POSITIVE
  Russia-Ukraine resolution:
    Commodity costs → POSITIVE (input deflation)
end note
GEO --> ORCH : Structured geopolitical sector tags
ORCH -> DB : Store geo_signals table\n(signal_type | sector | score | source | as_of_date)
DB --> ORCH : Stored
end

group 2. Policy & Regulatory Signal Collection
ORCH -> POL : Collect India policy and regulatory signals
POL -> GEOAPI : Fetch RBI MPC minutes / decisions
GEOAPI --> POL : Rate trajectory signals
POL -> GEOAPI : Fetch PIB / Budget / PLI scheme updates
GEOAPI --> POL : Fiscal and policy signals
POL -> NET : Fetch SEBI regulatory announcements
NET --> POL : Regulatory change signals
note right of POL
  Policy Signal Types:
  RBI rate cut cycle  → Banking / NBFC POSITIVE
  PLI expansion       → Target sector POSITIVE
  Budget capex boost  → Infra / Defence POSITIVE
  SEBI tightening     → Broking NEGATIVE
  State election win  → Consumption POSITIVE
  GST rate change     → Sector-specific impact
end note
POL --> ORCH : Structured policy sector tags
ORCH -> DB : Store policy_signals table
DB --> ORCH : Stored
end

group 3. FII / DII Flow Sentiment
ORCH -> FLOW : Analyze FII / DII flow patterns
FLOW -> GEOAPI : Fetch NSDL daily FII/DII flow data
GEOAPI --> FLOW : Net buy / sell by FII and DII (30-day)
note right of FLOW
  Flow Signal Rules [Deterministic]:
  FII selling + DII buying → ACCUMULATION signal
    (Smart money divergence — contrarian positive)
  FII buying heavily → CAUTION
    (Late cycle — momentum may be exhausted)
  Both selling → RISK OFF signal
  DII selling + FII buying → MIXED signal
  Sustained FII outflow > 3 months → macro headwind
end note
FLOW --> ORCH : Flow sentiment score + divergence signal
ORCH -> DB : Store flow_signals table
DB --> ORCH : Stored
end

group 4. Contrarian Sentiment Detection
ORCH -> CONTRA : Detect contrarian opportunity signals
CONTRA -> NET : Scan sector / stock sentiment in media
NET --> CONTRA : Sentiment data across sectors
CONTRA -> FIN : Fetch 52-week high/low data per sector
FIN --> CONTRA : Price range context
note right of CONTRA
  Contrarian Signal Rules:
  Sector down > 20% from 52w high AND
  fundamentals intact → BUY ZONE
  Media narrative "sector is doomed" AND
  no structural change → CONTRARIAN POSITIVE
  Excessive analyst upgrades on sector → CAUTION
  Retail investor euphoria signals → TRIM ZONE
  India negative in Western media AND
  domestic data contradicts → OFTEN BUY SIGNAL
end note
CONTRA --> ORCH : Contrarian opportunity map\nby sector with confidence score
ORCH -> DB : Store contrarian_signals table
DB --> ORCH : Stored
end

group 5. Signal Aggregation
ORCH -> SIGAGG : Aggregate all signals into unified view
SIGAGG -> DB : Load geo / policy / flow / contrarian signals
DB --> SIGAGG : All signal tables
note right of SIGAGG
  Aggregation Priority Order:
  1. User macro thesis override (absolute highest)
  2. Geopolitical structural signals (long lag, high alpha)
  3. Policy / regulatory signals (medium lag)
  4. FII/DII flow signals (short lag)
  5. Contrarian sentiment (entry timing)

  Output: unified sector conviction scores
  STRONG_BUY / BUY / NEUTRAL / AVOID / STRONG_AVOID
end note
SIGAGG --> ORCH : Unified sector conviction map\n(sector | conviction | primary_signal_source |\nconfidence | horizon)
ORCH -> DB : Store unified_signals table
DB --> ORCH : Stored
end

== FLOW 1 : PORTFOLIO INGESTION ==

group 6. User Portfolio Input
User -> UI : Upload CAMS PDF / enter MF holdings
User -> UI : Enter ETF + direct equity holdings
User -> UI : Optional: Enter manual macro thesis override
UI -> ORCH : Trigger ingestion with context
ORCH -> DB : Store user_macro_thesis
DB --> ORCH : Stored
end

group 7. MF and ETF Ingestion
ORCH -> MFP : Parse MF holdings
MFP -> MFINPUT : Read CAMS PDF / manual input
MFINPUT --> MFP : Fund names / values / scheme codes
MFP -> FUNDAPI : Fetch top-10 holdings per fund
FUNDAPI --> MFP : Fund -> stock -> weight (AMFI monthly)
MFP --> ORCH : Parsed MF stock exposure

ORCH -> ETFA : Decompose ETF holdings
ETFA -> ETFINPUT : Read ETF input
ETFINPUT --> ETFA : ETF names / units
ETFA -> FUNDAPI : Fetch ETF constituents
FUNDAPI --> ETFA : ETF -> stock -> weight
ETFA --> ORCH : Parsed ETF exposure
end

group 8. Normalization and Overlap Analysis
ORCH -> NORM : Normalize all instrument exposure
note right of NORM
  Normalization Rules:
  1. Map names to NSE symbols
     "HDFC Bank Ltd" = "HDFCBANK"
  2. Deduplicate across MF/ETF/direct
  3. Aggregate weights per stock
  4. Standardize sector classification
  5. Handle name variants
end note
NORM -> DB : Read direct equity holdings
DB --> NORM : Existing stocks
NORM --> ORCH : Normalized exposure map
ORCH -> DB : Store normalized_exposure table
DB --> ORCH : Stored

ORCH -> OVL : Compute overlap scores
OVL -> DB : Load normalized exposure
DB --> OVL : Exposure map
note right of OVL
  Overlap Thresholds [Hard Rules]:
  > 3%  → HARD EXCLUDE
  1-3%  → FLAG for LLM override
  0.5-1%→ YELLOW
  < 0.5%→ GREEN — genuine addition
end note
OVL --> ORCH : Overlap scores per stock
ORCH -> DB : Store overlap_scores
DB --> ORCH : Stored

ORCH -> GAP : Identify sector gaps
GAP -> DB : Read exposure + unified_signals
DB --> GAP : Portfolio map + signal conviction
GAP --> ORCH : Gap sectors ranked by:\n1. Portfolio underweight AND\n2. Signal conviction score
ORCH -> DB : Store identified_gaps
DB --> ORCH : Stored
end

group 9. Monthly Data Refresh
REFRESH -> ORCH : Monthly cron trigger
ORCH -> MFP : Re-fetch AMFI holdings
MFP -> FUNDAPI : Latest monthly data
FUNDAPI --> MFP : Updated holdings
MFP --> ORCH : Refreshed MF exposure
ORCH -> ETFA : Re-fetch ETF constituents
ETFA -> FUNDAPI : Latest ETF data
FUNDAPI --> ETFA : Updated ETF holdings
ETFA --> ORCH : Refreshed ETF exposure
ORCH -> NORM : Re-normalize
NORM --> ORCH : Updated exposure
ORCH -> OVL : Recompute overlap
OVL --> ORCH : Updated overlap scores
ORCH -> DB : Update all portfolio tables
DB --> ORCH : Refreshed
end

== FLOW 2 : NEW BUY RECOMMENDATION ==

group 10. User Buy Request + MANDATORY Portfolio Context Load
User -> UI : Select index / horizon / risk / top N
UI -> ORCH : Start new-buy analysis

note over ORCH
  MANDATORY GATE — Cannot proceed without portfolio context.
  New Buy recommendations are ALWAYS personalised
  to existing holdings. Generic recommendations
  without portfolio context are blocked.
end note

ORCH -> DB : Check portfolio_last_updated timestamp
DB --> ORCH : Portfolio freshness status

alt Portfolio exists and is fresh (< 35 days old)
    ORCH -> DB : Load FULL portfolio context:\n- normalized_exposure (all MF + ETF + direct stocks)\n- overlap_scores (per stock)\n- identified_gaps (sector gaps)\n- unified_signals (geo + policy + flow)\n- user_macro_thesis\n- direct_equity holdings\n- sector concentration summary
    DB --> ORCH : Complete portfolio intelligence bundle
    ORCH -> UI : Show portfolio summary to user:\n"Analysing against your ₹X portfolio\n(Y MFs, Z direct stocks, last updated DD/MM/YY)"
    UI --> User : Portfolio context confirmed — proceeding
else Portfolio missing or stale
    ORCH -> UI : Block buy flow — portfolio update required
    UI --> User : "Your portfolio data is missing or older\nthan 35 days. Please upload latest CAMS\nstatement before new buy analysis."
    User -> UI : Upload fresh CAMS PDF
    UI -> ORCH : Trigger Flow 1 Portfolio Ingestion first
    note over ORCH
      Re-run complete ingestion pipeline:
      MFP → AMFI fetch → NORM → OVL → GAP
      before resuming buy flow
    end note
    ORCH -> DB : Store refreshed portfolio data
    DB --> ORCH : Portfolio updated
    ORCH -> DB : Reload full portfolio context
    DB --> ORCH : Fresh portfolio intelligence bundle
end

ORCH -> DB : Load unified_signals
DB --> ORCH : Current geo + policy + flow signals
end

group 11. Universe Discovery
ORCH -> IDX : Fetch index members
IDX -> MKT : Get constituents
MKT --> IDX : Index members
IDX --> ORCH : Universe list
end

group 12. Signal-Aware Industry Recommendation — Portfolio Gap Weighted
ORCH -> IND : Identify preferred industries
IND -> DB : Load unified sector conviction scores
DB --> IND : Geo + policy + flow signal map
IND -> DB : Load identified_gaps — sectors underweight in portfolio
DB --> IND : Gap sectors ranked by portfolio underweight %
IND -> DB : Load sector_concentration — sectors already overweight
DB --> IND : Sectors to avoid due to existing exposure
IND -> NET : Validate with current market signals
NET --> IND : Latest sector confirmation signals
note right of IND
  Industry Selection Logic [Portfolio-First]:
  Score = (Signal Conviction × 0.4) +
          (Portfolio Gap Weight × 0.35) +
          (Current Market Signal × 0.25)

  Hard exclusions before scoring:
  - Sectors where portfolio already > 25% → SKIP
    (already covered by MF + direct holdings)
  - Sectors flagged STRONG_AVOID → SKIP

  Example for your portfolio:
  Private Banking already 6% via MFs → SKIP
  Defence at 0% + geo tailwind → PRIORITISE
  CDMO at 0% + structural thesis → PRIORITISE

  Output includes explicit reason why each
  sector was selected or excluded
end note

IND -> LLMSMART : industry_reasoning(\n  sectors, macro_thesis, portfolio_summary\n)
note right of LLMSMART
  Sonnet generates a 3-4 sentence strategic rationale
  explaining sector prioritization to the investor.
  One call per buy session (low volume).
  Fallback: deterministic sector score description.
end note
LLMSMART --> IND : Sector prioritization narrative

IND --> ORCH : Ranked industries with composite score\n+ reason: gap / signal / exclusion\n+ LLM sector rationale
end

group 13. Portfolio-Aware Candidate Generation
ORCH -> CAND : Filter universe by preferred industries
CAND -> DB : Load existing direct equity holdings
DB --> CAND : Stocks already held directly
CAND -> DB : Load MF top holdings (normalized_exposure)
DB --> CAND : All stocks already owned via MFs
note right of CAND
  Candidate Pre-filter [Hard Rules]:
  Remove any stock where:
  1. Already held directly (avoid doubling up)
  2. Overlap score > 3% across MF holdings
  3. Sector already at hard concentration limit

  This ensures every candidate that reaches
  quant scoring is GENUINELY NEW exposure
  not already in portfolio via any instrument
end note
CAND -> FIN : Get fundamentals / price data\nfor pre-filtered candidates only
FIN --> CAND : Raw candidate data
CAND --> ORCH : Pre-filtered candidate stock set\n(guaranteed new exposure only)
end

group 14. Quality Moat Quant Scoring
ORCH -> QBUY : Score on quality moat factors
note right of QBUY
  Quality Moat Weights:
  ROCE > 18% sustained 5yr      → 25%
  Free Cash Flow positive 4/5yr → 25%
  Revenue growth consistency    → 20%
  Promoter holding stable/rising→ 15%
  Debt / Equity < 0.5           → 15%

  Bonus adjustments:
  +5% if geopolitical tailwind confirmed
  +5% if FII/DII accumulation detected
  -10% if governance flag raised
end note
QBUY -> FIN : Fetch 5yr financials / ratios
FIN --> QBUY : Factor data
QBUY --> ORCH : Quality-moat scored universe
end

group 15. Multi-Source Risk Filtering
ORCH -> RFILT : Apply hard risk filters
RFILT -> DB : Read overlap + concentration
DB --> RFILT : Portfolio context
RFILT -> FIN : Check liquidity + volatility
FIN --> RFILT : Volume / beta / std deviation
RFILT -> NET : Check governance flags
NET --> RFILT : Promoter pledging / SEBI alerts
note right of RFILT
  Hard Exclusion Rules:
  Avg daily vol < ₹5Cr      → illiquid
  Beta > 2.0                → excessive volatility
  Promoter pledge > 50%     → governance risk
  SEBI action in last 12m   → exclude
  Sector concentration > 30%→ exclude
  Geo signal = STRONG_AVOID → exclude
end note
RFILT --> ORCH : Risk-filtered candidates
end

group 16. Shortlist Selection
ORCH -> TOPN : Select top N candidates
TOPN --> ORCH : Initial shortlist
end

group 17. Qualitative Validation — LLM:Sonnet [UPGRADED]
loop For each shortlisted stock
    ORCH -> VALID : Validate score and suitability
    VALID -> FIN : Recheck financials
    FIN --> VALID : Financial validation
    VALID -> NET : Check news / events / sentiment
    NET --> VALID : News signals
    VALID -> DB : Check geo/policy signal alignment
    DB --> VALID : Signal context for this sector

    VALID -> LLMSMART : qualitative_analysis(\n  candidate, news, signal_context\n)
    note right of LLMSMART
      Sonnet returns structured JSON:
      {
        "approved": true|false,
        "confidence": 0.0-1.0,
        "reasoning": "..."
      }
      Temperature 0.1 — deterministic, auditable output.
      Per-stock call (low volume — Sonnet justified).
      Fallback: rule-based sentiment scoring if LLM unavailable.
    end note
    LLMSMART --> VALID : JSON validation result

    alt Stock approved (LLM or fallback)
        VALID --> ORCH : Approved with confidence score
    else Rejected or reduced confidence
        VALID --> ORCH : Reject / reduce confidence
        ORCH -> TOPN : Request replacement
        TOPN --> ORCH : Next-best candidate
    end
end
end

group 18. Portfolio Differentiation — MF Holdings Aware
ORCH -> DIFF : Filter for genuine differentiation
DIFF -> DB : Load overlap_scores for shortlisted stocks
DB --> DIFF : Per-stock overlap scores
DIFF -> DB : Load normalized_exposure —\nwhich MFs already own each shortlisted stock
DB --> DIFF : Fund-level ownership detail per stock
DIFF -> DB : Load identified_gaps — what is genuinely missing
DB --> DIFF : Confirmed gap sectors
note right of DIFF
  Step 1 — Deterministic Hard Overlap Rules:
  HARD EXCLUDE: overlap > 3% across all MFs + ETFs
  FLAG: overlap 1-3% → LLM decides with high bar

  Step 2 — Fund Attribution Check:
  For each remaining candidate, identify:
  "Which of your funds already owns this stock
   and at what weight?"
  This makes the recommendation transparent

  Step 3 — LLM Differentiation Scoring:
  Score each stock on genuine portfolio add value
  Penalise stocks that duplicate existing exposure
  even if overlap score is technically under 3%

  Step 4 — Signal Alignment:
  Does this stock benefit from current geo/policy?
  Score +/- accordingly

  Output explicitly states for each stock:
  GENUINELY NEW: "Not held in any of your funds"
  MARGINAL ADD: "Held in [Fund X] at 0.8% — small overlap"
  EXCLUDED: "Already 2.75% in your portfolio via [Fund Y]"
end note
DIFF --> ORCH : Complementary shortlist with:\n- overlap score\n- fund attribution detail\n- differentiation rationale\n- signal alignment score
end

group 19. Contrarian Entry Timing
ORCH -> TIMING : Validate entry timing
TIMING -> FIN : Price trend / momentum / 52w range
FIN --> TIMING : Technical inputs
TIMING -> NET : Recent market-moving news
NET --> TIMING : Catalyst signals
TIMING -> DB : Load contrarian_signals + flow_signals
DB --> TIMING : Contrarian and flow context
note right of TIMING
  Entry Decision Matrix:
  Quality stock + geo tailwind + contrarian signal
    → STRONG ENTER NOW
  Quality stock + geo tailwind + no contrarian signal
    → ACCUMULATE in tranches
  Quality stock + neutral geo + contrarian signal
    → ENTER with smaller initial position
  Quality stock + geo headwind
    → WAIT — monitor for signal change
  Any stock + STRONG_AVOID signal
    → DO NOT ENTER regardless of quant score
end note
TIMING --> ORCH : Entry signal per stock:\nSTRONG ENTER / ACCUMULATE /\nSMALL INITIAL / WAIT / DO NOT ENTER
end

group 20. Position Sizing with Signal Weighting
ORCH -> SIZING : Calculate conviction-weighted sizes
SIZING -> DB : Load direct equity allocation +\ninvestable surplus + entry signals
DB --> SIZING : Allocation context
note right of SIZING
  Sizing Rules [Deterministic]:
  Highest conviction + geo tailwind  → 25-30%
  High conviction + neutral signal   → 20-25%
  Medium conviction                  → 15-20%
  Toe-hold / monitor                 → 5-10%

  Tranche rule:
  Never deploy full position at once
  Split into 2-3 tranches over 4-8 weeks
  Reduces timing risk on entry

  Hard Limits:
  Max single stock        → 30%
  Max total direct picks  → 4 stocks
  Total direct equity     → max 20-25% of
                            overall portfolio
end note
SIZING --> ORCH : Allocation % + tranche schedule per stock
end

group 21. Tax & Transaction Cost Impact Assessment
ORCH -> TAX : Assess tax and cost impact
TAX -> DB : Load existing holdings + purchase dates
DB --> TAX : Holding period per existing stock
note right of TAX
  Tax Rules [India - Deterministic]:
  STCG (held < 1yr): 20% on gains
  LTCG (held > 1yr): 12.5% above ₹1.25L
  Dividend: taxed at slab rate

  Cost Rules:
  Brokerage + STT + stamp duty ~ 0.1-0.2%
  Frequent churn erodes returns

  Output:
  Flag any SELL that would trigger STCG
  Suggest holding to LTCG threshold if
  thesis still intact
  Include net-of-tax return estimate
  in final recommendation
end note
TAX -> FIN : Fetch current prices for cost basis calc
FIN --> TAX : Current market prices
TAX --> ORCH : Tax impact per position +\nnet-of-tax return projections +\nSTCG / LTCG flags
end

group 22. Data Freshness and Confidence
ORCH -> CONF : Validate all data freshness
CONF -> DB : Check all table timestamps
DB --> CONF : Freshness status
CONF -> FIN : Check market data recency
FIN --> CONF : Data age
CONF -> NET : Check signal recency
NET --> CONF : News freshness
alt All data fresh
    CONF --> ORCH : Confidence GREEN — proceed
else Stale data detected
    CONF --> ORCH : Stale warning — re-trigger ingestion
    ORCH -> MFP : Re-fetch holdings
    MFP -> FUNDAPI : Latest AMFI data
    FUNDAPI --> MFP : Refreshed
    MFP --> ORCH : Updated
    ORCH -> OVL : Recompute overlap
    OVL --> ORCH : Updated scores
    CONF --> ORCH : Confidence YELLOW — proceed with caveat
end
end

group 23. Final Recommendation — Portfolio-Personalised Output [LLM:Haiku + Cached]
ORCH -> BUY : Finalize buy recommendations
BUY -> DB : Load final portfolio context for output generation
DB --> BUY : Full holdings + overlap + gaps + signals

loop For each approved recommendation
    BUY -> LLMFAST : buy_rationale(\n  item, portfolio_context\n)\n[system prompt cached]
    note right of LLMFAST
      Haiku generates a 2-3 sentence personalized rationale.
      System prompt is cached — ~90% input token cost saving
      across all per-stock calls in same session.
      Temperature 0.25, max_tokens 220.
      Fallback: deterministic template rationale.
    end note
    LLMFAST --> BUY : Personalized rationale string
end

note right of BUY
  Every recommendation output is personalised:
  Shows exactly WHY this stock is recommended
  FOR THIS SPECIFIC PORTFOLIO — not generically

  Output must include for each stock:
  "You already own X% of this sector via [Fund Name]
   This stock adds [specific gap] not covered by
   your existing holdings"
end note
BUY --> ORCH : Final 3-4 stocks with:\n- 18-30 month investment thesis\n- "Why this stock for YOUR portfolio" rationale (LLM)\n- Geopolitical tailwind / headwind assessment\n- Exact overlap score vs YOUR MF/ETF holdings\n- Which specific MFs already own this stock\n- Sector gap being filled in YOUR portfolio\n- Quality moat score\n- Entry signal (STRONG ENTER / ACCUMULATE / WAIT)\n- Tranche deployment schedule\n- Suggested allocation % of YOUR direct equity corpus\n- Net-of-tax return projection\n- Data confidence band (GREEN / YELLOW)\n- Sectors NOT recommended + reason (already covered)
ORCH --> UI : Full portfolio-personalised recommendation
UI --> User : Display with portfolio context panel:\n"Your current exposure vs recommended addition"\nshown side by side for each recommendation
end

== FLOW 3 : PORTFOLIO MONITORING ==

group 24. Monitoring Trigger
User -> UI : Start monitoring

note over UI
  MANDATORY OVERLAP GATE — enforced before monitoring runs.
  UI checks overlap_scores table for rows with
  updated_at within the last 35 days.
  If none found → block run with warning:
  "Portfolio context missing. Please upload
   CAMS statement first."
  st.stop() prevents button from rendering.
end note

alt Fresh overlap scores exist (updated_at < 35 days ago)
    UI -> ORCH : Monitor portfolio
    ORCH -> SIGREF : Refresh signal intelligence first
    SIGREF -> DB : Trigger signal pipeline re-run\n(geo / policy / flow / contrarian)
    DB --> SIGREF : Confirmed
    SIGREF --> ORCH : Signals refreshed before monitoring begins
    ORCH -> DB : Load portfolio + latest signals
    DB --> ORCH : Full context
else No fresh overlap scores
    UI --> User : "Portfolio context missing.\nPlease upload CAMS statement first."
    note over UI
      st.stop() — monitoring button never rendered.
      User must complete Flow 1 ingestion first.
    end note
end
end

group 25. Industry Monitoring [SIGNAL AWARE]
loop For each portfolio stock
    ORCH -> PIND : Assess industry outlook
    PIND -> NET : Latest industry signals
    NET --> PIND : Industry developments
    PIND -> DB : Load geo/policy signals for this sector
    DB --> PIND : Signal context
    PIND --> ORCH : Industry assessment with\nsignal alignment score
end
end

group 26. Stock Monitoring
loop For each portfolio stock
    ORCH -> PSTK : Assess individual stock
    PSTK -> FIN : Financial / price / performance data
    FIN --> PSTK : Stock metrics
    PSTK -> NET : Company news / sentiment / events
    NET --> PSTK : Company signals
    PSTK --> ORCH : Stock assessment
end
end

group 27. Portfolio Quant Re-Scoring
loop For each portfolio stock
    ORCH -> QMON : Recalculate quality moat score
    note right of QMON
      Overall quant score = quality (80%) + valuation (20%):
      ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
      ROCE 5yr component         × 0.35
      FCF positive years         × 0.25
      Revenue consistency        × 0.20
      P/E score (sub-model)      × 0.20
      ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
      P/E score — weighted relative comparison (NOT absolute threshold):
        40%: stock trailing P/E vs own 5yr avg P/E
             clamp(1 - (pe_trailing - pe_5yr_avg) / pe_5yr_avg, 0, 1)
             trading below own history = good
        35%: stock trailing P/E vs sector peer P/E
             clamp(1 - (pe_trailing - sector_pe) / sector_pe, 0, 1)
             discount to peers = good
        25%: forward P/E vs trailing P/E
             clamp(2 - pe_forward / pe_trailing, 0, 1)
             forward < trailing = earnings growth expected = good
      ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
      PE fields per stock: pe_trailing, pe_5yr_avg,
      sector_pe, pe_forward (from get_financials).
    end note
    QMON --> ORCH : Updated quant score (quality + P/E blend)
end
end

group 28. Thesis Review — LLM:Sonnet [UPGRADED]
loop For each portfolio stock
    ORCH -> PREV : Review thesis status
    note right of PREV
      Thesis Breach Hard Rules (always enforced):
      SELL regardless of P&L if:
      - Management change / fraud signal
      - ROCE drops below 12% two quarters
      - Promoter pledge spikes above 40%
      - Geo signal flips to STRONG_AVOID
        for this stock's sector
      - Original macro thesis no longer valid
      - Structural sector disruption confirmed
      No price anchoring permitted
    end note
    PREV -> FIN : Recheck financials
    FIN --> PREV : Metrics
    PREV -> NET : Recheck risks / catalysts
    NET --> PREV : Signals
    PREV -> DB : Check if geo signals changed
    DB --> PREV : Latest signal for sector

    PREV -> LLMSMART : thesis_review(\n  holding, quant_score,\n  sector_signal, stock_news\n)
    note right of LLMSMART
      Sonnet evaluates nuanced multi-signal thesis.
      Returns structured JSON:
      {
        "status": "INTACT"|"WEAKENED"|"BREACHED",
        "reasoning": "..."
      }
      Hard rules (STRONG_AVOID, ROCE < 0.3) override LLM.
      Temperature 0.1 — deterministic, auditable.
      Fallback: rule-based quant threshold check.
    end note
    LLMSMART --> PREV : JSON thesis assessment

    PREV --> ORCH : Score + thesis:\nINTACT / WEAKENED / BREACHED +\ngeo signal change flag +\nLLM reasoning
end
end

group 29. Drawdown and Risk Alert
ORCH -> DRAW : Check portfolio drawdown and risk levels
DRAW -> FIN : Fetch current prices for all holdings
FIN --> DRAW : Current market values
DRAW -> DB : Load purchase prices + position sizes
DB --> DRAW : Cost basis data
note right of DRAW
  Drawdown Alert Rules [Deterministic]:
  Single stock down > 20% from entry:
    → Flag for thesis review
  Single stock down > 35% from entry:
    → Force thesis review + SELL consideration
  Portfolio down > 15% overall:
    → Risk-off alert to user
  Single position now > 35% of portfolio
  due to others falling:
    → Rebalancing flag

  These are alerts only — Decision Agent
  makes final call with thesis context
end note
DRAW --> ORCH : Drawdown alerts + concentration flags
end

group 30. Portfolio Action Decision
loop For each portfolio stock
    ORCH -> DEC : Decide action
    note right of DEC
      Decision inputs:
      - Updated quant score
      - Thesis status (INTACT/WEAKENED/BREACHED)
      - Geo / policy signal alignment
      - Drawdown alerts
      - Sector concentration
      - STCG / LTCG tax implications
      - No price anchoring enforced
    end note
    DEC --> ORCH : BUY MORE / HOLD / TRIM /\nSELL / REPLACE + rationale
end
ORCH --> UI : Consolidated actions
UI --> User : Show decisions table with columns:\nsymbol | action | severity | overlap_pct | rationale\n(overlap_pct joined from overlap_scores —\nimmediately shows why a stock is flagged,\ne.g. HDFCBANK ~3.1% triggers reject logic)
end

group 31. Behavioural Guard Check
ORCH -> BGUARD : Screen decisions for behavioural bias
note right of BGUARD
  Behavioural Bias Rules [Hard Checks]:
  If user tries to override SELL on breached thesis:
    → Block and show breach evidence
  If user tries to add 5th direct stock:
    → Block — max 4 rule enforcement
  If same stock sold and rebought within 30 days:
    → Flag as emotional reversal pattern
  If user increases position after 20% loss
  without thesis confirmation:
    → Flag as averaging-down trap
  If monitoring frequency > 3x per day:
    → Show "check less, earn more" reminder
end note
BGUARD --> ORCH : Bias flags + override blocks
ORCH --> UI : Show behavioural guardrail alerts
UI --> User : Display bias warnings\nbefore any override is accepted
end

group 32. Monitoring Rationale + Replace Feedback Loop [LLM:Haiku + Cached]
loop For each action
    ORCH -> LLMFAST : monitoring_rationale(\n  action_row, thesis, drawdown\n)\n[system prompt cached]
    note right of LLMFAST
      Haiku returns STRICT JSON — not free text:
      {
        "action":   "HOLD"|"BUY MORE"|"TRIM"|"SELL"|"REPLACE",
        "severity": "LOW"|"MEDIUM"|"HIGH"|"CRITICAL",
        "rationale": "1-2 sentence explanation"
      }

      Why JSON: free-text rationale starting with a directive
      word (e.g. "REJECT" or "BUY MORE") would pollute the
      action field if parsed naively. Strict JSON eliminates
      the parsing ambiguity entirely.

      Parser validates action + severity against allowed enums.
      Falls back to deterministic decide_actions() values if
      JSON parse fails — no action row is ever dropped.

      System prompt cached across all 50+ calls per session.
      Temperature 0.2, max_tokens 200.
    end note
    LLMFAST --> ORCH : dict {action, severity, rationale}\nor None (fallback to deterministic)
end

alt Any stock flagged SELL or REPLACE
    ORCH -> DB : Update exposure — remove exited stock
    DB --> ORCH : Updated
    ORCH -> OVL : Recompute overlap with updated portfolio
    OVL --> ORCH : Refreshed overlap + new gaps
    ORCH -> DB : Update overlap_scores + identified_gaps
    DB --> ORCH : Updated
    ORCH -> UI : Auto-prompt Flow 2 new buy\nwith refreshed context pre-loaded
    UI --> User : "Portfolio gap created.\nRun new buy recommendation?"
end
end

@enduml
